{"meta":{"authors":[{"fullname":"José I. Cabezón","id":"7"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:09:33 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:09:33 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"title":""},{"title":"Description","index":1,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p>Many of these rituals have as their goal the general protection of individuals or communities from disease (nad), evil spirits (gdon) and obstacles (bar chad), but protection rituals can also have more specific foci. They rely on a variety of deities, both supramundane and mundane, but typically involve protector deities.<\/p> "},{"title":"Related Terms","index":2,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p>bsrung ba'i cho ga, skyob pa'i cho ga<\/p> "},{"title":"Example Texts","index":3,"parent_index":0,"body":" <ul> <li>See TBRC topic T2600 (nad gdon bar chad spyir srung ba, \"protection from <span>disease, evil spirits, and obstacles<\/span>\"<a class=\"text-link-search\" href=\"http:\/\/www.tbrc.org\/kb\/tbrc-detail.xq;jsessionid=AD429F060F9FB794398ADE9B0E6D9659?RID=T2600\"><\/a>).<\/li> <\/ul> "},{"title":"Secondary Sources","index":4,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 <\/xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <\/xml><![endif]--><!--[if !mso]> <span class=\"mceItemObject\" classid=\"clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D\" id=ieooui> <\/span> <mce:style><! st1\\:*{behavior:url(#i<![endif]--> <!--[endif]--><!-- --><!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><! \/* Style Definitions *\/ table.MsoNormalTable {mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; mso-style-noshow:yes; mso-style-parent:\"\"; mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; mso-para-margin:0in; mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:10.0pt; font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; mso-ansi-language:#0400; mso-fareast-language:#0400; mso-bidi-language<![endif]--> <!--[endif]--><\/p> <p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocum